CHAPTER 4 IMPLEMENTATION AND RESULT ANALYSIS

4.1   Application Interface
The ARPx tool features a professional dark-themed graphical user interface (GUI) built with Python Tkinter. The interface provides three main panels: a Network Scanner panel at the top for subnet input and host discovery, an ARP Spoof Control panel in the middle for target/gateway configuration and attack control, and a live console log at the bottom displaying timestamped events, alerts, and status messages.
All network operations run in background threads via the threading.Thread class, ensuring the interface remains responsive at all times. GUI updates from background threads are safely routed through the root.after() method to avoid cross-thread Tkinter violations.
