4.4   Security & Ethical Considerations
IMPORTANT: This tool must only be used on networks where explicit written authorization has been obtained. Unauthorized ARP spoofing is a criminal offence under the Information Technology Act, 2000 (India) and equivalent laws in other jurisdictions.
•	ARP Restoration on Stop: ARPx automatically restores correct entries when spoofing is halted — a responsible design choice that prevents unintended network disruption.
•	No Data Exfiltration: The tool only redirects ARP entries. No credential sniffing or packet capture functionality is implemented.
•	Isolated Test Network: All testing was performed on a closed VirtualBox Host-Only network with no internet or production network exposure.
•	Educational Purpose Only: The project is submitted as university coursework to understand network vulnerabilities and is not intended for malicious use.


